#
# Coin Collection
# This is for an Installment of Tablesmith Tuesday @ http://randomdm.wordpress.com
# A part of the Hoard Project my goal is to build a set of tables that will answer
# the question of if you can build a plot hooks out of loot by using random tables.
# This table builds a Numismatic Collection of coins, which begs the question, why
# would someone collect these coins?
#
# Groups:
# [Coin Type]	 			[Collection Type]			[Collection Miscellaneous]
# [Collection Year]			[Collection Origin]			[Subject]
# [Collection Subject]		[Collection Composition]	[Organization]
# [Collection Size]			[Coin Age]					[Coin Condition]
#
# Other .tab Calls
# [Miscellaneous.Size A]	[Miscellaneous.Weight]		[Miscellaneous.Language]
# [Miscellaneous.Shape]		[Miscellaneous.Ruler]		[Countries.Start]


%iSize%,0
%sCollectionSize%,0
%sCondition%,0
%sConditionDesc%,0
%iConditionValue%,0
%iAgeValue%,0
%sAge%,0
%sOrganization%,0
%sCollection%,0
%sCollectionType%,0
%sCollectionSubject%,0
%sCoinOrigin%,0
%sCollectionComposition%,0

:Start
1,[Generate]
_ [Display]

:Generate
1,|sCollectionSize=[Collection Size]|
_ |sCondition=[Coin Condition]|
_ |sAge=[Coin Age]|
_ |sOrganization=[Organization]|
_ |sCollectionType=[Collection Type]|

:Display
1,A %sCollectionSize% amount of coins %sOrganization%<br>
_ The coins are %sAge% in (%sCondition%)<br>
_Collection Identifier: %sCollectionType%<br>

;Collection Type
1,|sCollection="Year"|																	[Collection Year]
1,|sCollection="Origin"|			|sCoinOrigin=[Countries.Generate]|					[Collection Origin]
1,|sCollection="Subject"|			|sCollectionSubject=[~Subject]|						[Collection Subject]
1,|sCollection="Composition"|		|sCollectionComposition=[~Miscellaneous.Metal]|		[Collection Composition]
1,|sCollection="Miscellaneous"|															[Collection Miscellaneous]	

;Collection Miscellaneous
1,all the coins seem to be of a [Miscellaneous.Size A] size
1,these coins are all of a [Miscellaneous.Weight] weight
1,the collection is made up of coins with a [Miscellaneous.Language] quote on them

;Collection Year
1,of varying origins, composition, and printings, the only thing seemingly tying the collection together is the printed year.
1,each coin in the collection spans a {Dice~1d10} years
1,the only rhyme to the collection are the years they a printed

;Collection Origin
1,all the coins are from %sCoinOrigin%
1,the coins are all from %sCoinOrigin%, from different dates, dynasties, with different faces
1,it is quickly evident that all the coins are from %sCoinOrigin%

;Subject
1,[Miscellaneous.Shape]
1,[Miscellaneous.Ruler]

;Collection Subject
1,all the coins seem to feature a print of %sCollectionSubject%
1,age, origin, compistion, are all seem random, the collection is built around the %sCollectionSubject% mark on the coin
1,it's a collection of coins featuring %sCollectionSubject%

;Collection Composition
1,all the coins seem to be made of %sCollectionComposition%
1,the only thing tying this collection together is the metal (%sCollectionComposition%)

;Organization
1,in piles
1,are scattered about
1,are bagged in pouches
1,are stored in chests
1,have arranged in stacks
1,has been bundled
1,is in heaps
1,has been organized in a pyramid
1,has been put in mounds
1,are stored in barrels

;Collection Size
1,tiny 		|iSize={Dice~1d10}|
1,small 	|iSize={Calc~{Dice~1d10}x10}|
1,medium 	|iSize={Calc~{Dice~1d10}x50}|
1,big	 	|iSize={Calc~{Dice~4d10}x100}|
1,large 	|iSize={Calc~{Dice~10d10}x100}|
1,huge	 	|iSize={Calc~{Dice~10d10}x1000}|

;Coin Age
1,Ancient
_|iAgeValue=2|
1,Antiquated
_|iAgeValue=1.5|
1,Old
_|iAgeValue=1.25|
1,Outdated
_|iAgeValue=0|
1,Modern
_|iAgeValue=0|
1,Freshly-Minted
_|iAgeValue=0|

;Coin Condition
1, Circulated - About Good 
_|sConditionDesc="Very heavily worn with portions of lettering, date, and legends worn smooth. The date may be barely readable."|
_|iConditionValue=.01|
1, Circulated - Good 
_|sConditionDesc="Heavily worn with design visible but faint in areas. Many details are flat."|
_|iConditionValue=.1|
1, Circulated - Very Good
_|sConditionDesc="Well worn with main features clear and bold although rather flat."| 
_|iConditionValue=.2|
1, Circulated - Fine
_|sConditionDesc="Moderate to considerable even wear. Entire design is bold with overall pleasing appearance."|
_|iConditionValue=.3|
1, Circulated - Very Fine 
_|sConditionDesc="Shows moderate wear on high points of design. All major details are clear."|
_|iConditionValue=.5|
1, Circulated - Choice Very Fine 
_|sConditionDesc="Light even wear on the surface and highest parts of the design. All lettering and major features are sharp."|
_|iConditionValue=.6|
1, Circulated - Extremely Fine 
_|sConditionDesc="Design is lightly worn throughout, but all features are sharp and well defined. Traces of luster may show."| 
_|iConditionValue=.7|
1, Circulated - Choice Extremely Fine
_|sConditionDesc="Light overall wear shows on highest points. All design details are very sharp. Some of the mint luster is evident."| 
_|iConditionValue=.8|
1, About Uncirculated
_|sConditionDesc="Has traces of light wear on many of the high points. At least half of the mint luster is still present."|
_|iConditionValue=1|
1, Choice About Uncirculated
_|sConditionDesc="Evidence of friction on design high points. Most of mint luster remains."|
_|iConditionValue=1.5|
1, Mint - Uncirculated
_|sConditionDesc="Has no trace of wear but may show a number of contact marks and surface may be spotted or lack some luster."| 
_|iConditionValue=2|
1, Mint - Uncirculated
_|sConditionDesc="Some distracting contact marks or blemishes in prime focal areas. Luster may be impaired."|
_|iConditionValue=3|
1, Mint - Choice Uncirculated
_|sConditionDesc="An above average Uncirculated coin that may be brilliant or lightly toned and has very few contact marks on the surface or rim. MS67 through MS62 indicate a slightly higher or lower grade of preservation."|
_|iConditionValue=4|
1, Mint - Perfect Uncirculated
_|sConditionDesc="Perfect new condition, showing no trace of wear. The finest quality possible, with no evidence of scratches, handling, or contact with other coins. Very few regular issue coins are ever found in this condition."| 
_|iConditionValue=5|
1, Proof
_|sConditionDesc="Surface may have several contact marks, hairlines, or light rubs. Luster may be dull and eye-appeal lacking."|
_|iConditionValue=6|
1, Attractive Proof
_|sConditionDesc="Reflective surfaces with only a few blemishes in secondary focal places. No major flaws."| 
_|iConditionValue=7|
1, Choice Proof 
_|sConditionDesc="Reflective surfaces with no noticeable blemishes or flaws. Few scattered barely noticeable marks or hairlines."|
_|iConditionValue=8|